<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Logs">Logs</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span id="Locations,_commands"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Locations.2C_commands">Locations, commands</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-2" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>Log files are created in various places throughout the lifecycle of installation and running of CDF and Suite(s).
</p><p>In this release there is:
</p>
<ul><li>Node level logging for the CDF system and Kubernetes layers</li>
<li>Cluster level logging for some but not all CDF core services</li>
<li>Cluster level logging for most but not all Suite services</li>
<li>Aggregation for CDF and suite logs (if suites perform local logging). Aggregation and forwarding is done by Fluentd.</li>
<li>Log rotation is performed by a dedicated log rotation Pod, running logrotate and/or custom script.</li></ul>
<p>Because of the various layers that make up the CDF, the logs are in a number of locations and/or require command execution to obtain.
</p><p>The table below describes more details about the CDF processes and components:
</p>
<a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table>
<tbody><tr>
<th><b>Type</b>
</th>
<th><b>Location or command</b>
</th>
<th><b>Contents</b>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>Location
</td>
<td>Linux syslog /var/log/messages / dmesg
</td>
<td>Kernel ring buffer contains some messages related to Docker and other host-level Kubernetes components: Kubelet and Kube-proxy.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Command
</td>
<td>docker logs &lt;container ID&gt;
</td>
<td>Stdout from inside a particular container. Same as &lt;CDF root&gt;/data/docker/containers but obtainable via command.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Command
</td>
<td>“journalctl -u &lt;unit name&gt;
</td>
<td>Set unit name to following:
<p>Docker: docker
</p><p>Kubectl logs: kubelet
</p><p>Kube-proxy logs: kube-proxy
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Location
</td>
<td>&lt;CDF root&gt;
</td>
<td>Installation logs
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Location
</td>
<td>&lt;CDF root&gt;/logs/
</td>
<td>Component logs for core Kubernetes components
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Location
</td>
<td>External NFS service
</td>
<td>CDF core and Suite logs
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Location
</td>
<td>/var/log/cdf
</td>
<td>CDF local logs collected by Fluentd
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Container_logs_in_pods">Container logs in pods</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-3" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-3" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>Pods can contain multiple containers. For kubectl commands, add –c &lt;name of container&gt; to get individual container logs.
</p><p>To see what containers are inside a Pod run kubectl describe pod &lt;name of pod&gt; then look for the Init containers: and containers: section to see what containers make up the pod. Then use the container name as the value for the –c option on kubectl describe.
</p>
<ol><li>kubectl describe pod mng-portal-2981853324-x8f29 -n core</li></ol>
<pre class="syntaxhighlighter-pre">…
Init Containers:
install:
…
Containers:
mng-portal:
…
kubernetes-vault-renew:
…
</pre>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Log_collection_and_forwarding">Log collection and forwarding</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-4" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-4" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>CDF installs Fluentd in a Kubernetes Daemonset, this means every cluster node runs an instance of Fluentd. The Fluentd Pod is responsible for collection logs from various CDF log locations and collect or forwards the logs. By default the logs are collected below /var/log/cdf.
<a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="pic30.png" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/4/45/pic30.png/900px-pic30.png" width="900" height="425" srcset="/mediawiki/images/thumb/4/45/pic30.png/1350px-pic30.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/4/45/pic30.png 2x" data-file-width="1506" data-file-height="712"></a>
Three sets of logs are being gathered:
</p>
<ul><li>Kubernetes host processes, Kubernetes containerized processes, Docker (1)</li>
<li>Container logs all Kubernetes workload (2)</li>
<li>Other logs from &lt;K8S_HOME&gt;/log</li></ul>
<p>The default output location is /var/log/cdf.
</p><p>In this output location, three subdirectories exist:
</p>
<ul><li>kubernetes: this will contain all logs from (1)</li>
<li>container: this will will contain all logs from (2)</li>
<li>cdf-deployments: this will contain all logs from (3)</li></ul>
<p>The structure of the source location log files is preserved in the output collection location.
The collection location is by default on a per-node basis. This means that the Fluentd daemon running on a node will collect all logs into /var/log/cdf on that node.
The /var/log/cdf location can be remounted as a shared volume. The supported storage is not limited to NFS. Any RW storage that can be mounted to /var/log/cdf can be used. If shared storage is used -when all the nodes mount the same storage- the logs are collected in a single location.
The log file names are preserved except that a YYYYMMDD indicator is added to the filename and the logs are rolled daily.
Alternatively, logging data can be forwarded to Operations Bridge Analytics (OBA) or Elasticsearch. Both products contain analytics tools to view and analyze the logs.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Log_rotation">Log rotation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-5" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-5" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>A log rotation pod is deployed using a Kubernetes Daemonset, therefore it runs on every node.
</p><p>Logs are either rotated or deleted, by default  5 sets of logs are kept and the retention period is 3 days. Both values are configurable.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="CDF_core">CDF core</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-6" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-6" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The logs can be found on the node itself under /var/log/cdf. This is the location where Fluentd collects logs into from various other locatins.
</p><p>Logs contained in this location are CDF core services and suite application logs such as Tomcat server and other logs.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Suite">Suite</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-7" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-7" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The logs can be found in /var/log/cdf and/or on the external volume. Assuming a base directory of /var/vols/suite, the path would be /var/vols/suite/*/*.log.
</p><p>Logs contained in this location are application container logs such as Tomcat server and other logs
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Configuring_log_rotation">Configuring log rotation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-8" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-8" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>DOCKER_OPTS&nbsp;in&nbsp;the &lt;CDF root&gt;/cfg/docker files includes these options:
</p><p><code>--log-opt max-size=10m --log-opt max-file=5</code>
</p>
<a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table>
<tbody><tr>
<th><b>Option</b>
</th>
<th><b>Comment</b>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>max-size=10m
</td>
<td>Every log file will grow until it reaches 10 MB. After that the log information will roll over into a subsequent file.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>max-file=5
</td>
<td>There will be a maximum of 5 rollover log files. When the 5<sup>th</sup> file reaches the max-size size, the rollover will start overwriting the oldest log file.
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>If you want to change these values then after changing these trigger a daemon configuration reload:
</p><p><code>systemctl daemon-reload</code>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Monitoring">Monitoring</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-9" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-9" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>See chapter “Monitoring”
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Support_tool">Support tool</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-10" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-10" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="support-dump_tool">support-dump tool</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-11" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-11" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The CDF includes a support tool that gathers the data discussed in the “Logs” chapter and adds additional data.
</p><p>The tool is located in &lt;CDF root&gt;/tools/support-tool and is called support-dump.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Tool_output">Tool output</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-12" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-12" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The compressed file that the support tool generates is encrypted and password-protected with a chosen password:
</p><p>&lt;CDF root&gt;/tools/support-tool/dmp/support_data_YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.aes
</p><p>It can be made readable again using the following command:
</p><p><code>dd if=&lt;filename&gt;.aes |openssl aes-256-ecb -d -k &lt;your_password&gt;|tar zxf -</code>
</p><p>A log file is generated below &lt;CDF root&gt;/tools/support-tool/dmp.
</p><p>Refer to the Suite installation/administration guide for detailed information.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Collected_data_and_intended_use">Collected data and intended use</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-13" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperSupportability&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-13" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The data is intended to be handed to Micro Focus support.
</p><p>The data is a mix of output from OS commands, Docker commands and log files.
</p><p>Its console output is also generated in report format.
</p><p>The following data is generated:
</p>
<ul><li>CDF version information</li>
<li>Docker version information</li>
<li>Kubernetes version information</li>
<li>CDF components version information</li>
<li>Workload Docker running containers (ID, image status, node)</li>
<li>Cluster nodes</li>
<li>Kubernetes pods (namespace, name, status, uptime, IP, node)</li>
<li>Containers by pod (namespace, pod, node, image, container, container ID)</li>
<li>All suite deployments (including deleted ones) (suite, version, namespace, deployment status, install data, NFS info)</li>
<li>Capability information of the deployed suite</li>
<li>Docker inspect output for all containers</li>
<li>Kubernetes cluster-info dump output</li>
<li>Docker describe of pods</li>
<li>Dump of the suite installer database</li>
<li>Dump of the suite deployment metadata</li>
<li>Output of various OS commands listed in &lt;CDF root&gt;/tools/support-tool/conf/supportdump.config.</li></ul>

